<item>
            <title>[SOLR-14854] Add root project name &quot;lucene-solr&quot; (avoid automatic root project naming)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14854</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Gradle does not work if repository cloned into solr directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;$ git clone https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr.git solr
$ cd solr
$ ./gradlew tasks
FAILURE: Build failed with an exception.

* What went wrong:
A problem occurred configuring root project &apos;solr&apos;.
&amp;gt; A problem occurred configuring project &apos;:solr&apos;.
   &amp;gt; This plugin doesn&apos;t work if the root project shares both group and name with a subproject. Consider adding the following to settings.gradle:
     rootProject.name = &apos;solr-root&apos;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
